The paper presents a neural architecture search algorithm for constructing compact reinforcement learning policies, which involves optimizing the structure of neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves optimization techniques such as evolutionary strategies (ES) and explores the use of neural networks for computer vision tasks, which could place it in the categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
